metadata.name: Minimalist #18
metadata.description:
This abstract art is produced by exercising concepts of minimalism. Each artwork is composed of simple figures and simple engaging colors. 

Each abstract art piece is generated to connect with a specific type of person. When the viewer sees an abstract image that resonates with him or her a connection is made. 

This artwork was produced using computer graphics software and randomly layerd images.

metadata.name: Spradow #22
metadata.description:
A girl ventured into a dark jungle and encountered spiders. As she tried to leave, the hills and woods seemed to move and block her escape. She became trapped in the jungle, and despite search efforts by others, she was never found. Legend has it that her cries can still be heard in the village for over thousands of years.

Pressing the “i” key will invert the colors of the artwork, allowing you to see it in negative mode. Use this feature to explore new perspectives on this already stunning piece. If you want to save your favorite iterations of the artwork, press S to save your current image as a high-resolution file. Alternatively, pressing T allows you to save just the transparent layer so that you can superimpose it onto other images or backgrounds easily.

metadata.name: Blocky-Neon #28
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Blocky-Neon' is a colorful play on perspective and geometry.

Each output plays with color, and the absence of color, highlighted by stark white lines against a dark background.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

metadata.name: Typing #84
metadata.description: This project is intentionally released anonymously to emphasize the art rather than the artist. I hope you enjoy!

metadata.name: RULES (for Elementary Cellular Automata) #403
metadata.description:
An important element of generative art is emergence. The most famous algorithm for this is probably Cellular Automata (CA).

However, numerous generative artists have created works using CA, which has lost its visual freshness and is like chewing gum that has lost its taste.

Although it is such a classic algorithm, adding my own little ideas to it and finding a new "flavor" is the reason why I code.

Here, the subject is 1D Elementary Cellular Automata, the simplest of all cellular automata. 1D Elementary Cellular Automata has 256 different rules, which change the shapes produced. This work aims to create more complex shapes by randomly selecting some of those rules and placing multiple of them on the screen.

The on/off of the CA cell is often likened to the behavior of living creatures.As of 2022, in the country where I live, prices are rising, wages are not increasing, and COVID-19 has not yet ended. I created this work with the image of people at the mercy of these various rules.

---

Screen click: Change rules
S key: Save png
L key: Show/hide grid

metadata.name: Organic Oeuvre #88
metadata.description:
First project on FXHash.

Entirely coded in p5js.

Stochastic strokes while ensuring randomness is consistent; uses 500+ color palettes.

The pieces created by this project are dynamic and change based on the size of the viewing window ("organic"), making each viewing experience unique. 

In case you find a bug, please consider it an easter egg! Write to me on twitter if you think it's a bug and I'll send another couple your way from my reserved :)

Press s to save the image in fullscreen.

metadata.name: Collage #17
metadata.description:
Inspired by traditional Japanese wagami design. We use the iconic patterns of our previous projects to recreate this artwork. All the patterns are generated first and then used to build the scene. 

In this project Aluan brings his delicate texture from his 'Chaos' series, Jinyao brings his beloved pattern from the 'Cloud' series and Wen brings his iconic pattern from the 'Maze'. 'Collage' is not just about mixing our style, but it is also about finding harmony among all the elements. 'Collage' is also about working together, in that we can create something that's difficult to achieve or imagine if we were working alone.

Each piece contains the patterns of all the 3 artists, each artist has a certain number of patterns with different colors. Depending which artist you get, his pattern will be shown as the primary color theme while the pattern of the other 2 artists turns into grayscale to make the primary pattern with color stand out. 

There are 7 different scenes included in this project, which are : Mountains, Waves, Lake, Hexagons, Tetrapods, Chrysanthemums and Lotus. We took great inspiration from the traditional Japanese design, and we discovered these are some of the most common elements in it. Therefore we decide to use them and reimagine them by mixing our patterns. 

The title 'Collage' doesn't only apply to the visual style, but also to the code as well. In this project we mixed p5.js and Vanilla JS. While Aluan and Jinyao work with their patterns in p5. Wen gathered the patterns and recreated the full scene in Vanilla JS.

metadata.description: Interactive real-time audiovisual proof-of-concept for fxhash beta. Tap to start. Tap outside lines to mute. Each mint is a unique generative audio loop with audioreactive visualization. Web Audio + p5js. Idlebit, 2021.

metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: CHX-1 #170
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.
